============================================================
  FAMOUS PEOPLE
============================================================

Name:          Ada Lovelace
Lived:         1815 - 1852
Nationality:   English
Field:         Computing
Known For:     First computer algorithm
Contribution:  Wrote first algorithm for Babbage's machine; recognized computing potential
Quote:         "The Analytical Engine weaves algebraic patterns."

Name:          Leonardo da Vinci
Lived:         1452 - 1519
Nationality:   Italian
Field:         Art/Science
Known For:     Mona Lisa, anatomy
Contribution:  Renaissance polymath; Mona Lisa; anatomical drawings; flying machine designs
Quote:         "Learning never exhausts the mind."

Name:          Marie Curie
Lived:         1867 - 1934
Nationality:   Polish-French
Field:         Chemistry/Physics
Known For:     Radioactivity
Contribution:  First woman Nobel laureate; Nobel in two sciences; discovered radium and polonium
Quote:         "Nothing in life is to be feared, only to be understood."

============================================================
  MATHEMATICS
============================================================

Theorem/Law:  Golden Ratio
Branch:       Geometry
Formula:      phi = (1+sqrt(5))/2 = 1.618...
Applications: Art, architecture, nature, design
Discoverer:   Ancient Greeks (500)

Theorem/Law:  Taylor Series
Branch:       Calculus
Formula:      f(x) = sum of f^n(a)/n! * (x-a)^n
Applications: Numerical computation, signal processing
Discoverer:   Brook Taylor (1715)

Theorem/Law:  Four Color Theorem
Branch:       Topology
Formula:      Any planar map needs at most 4 colors
Applications: Cartography, graph coloring
Discoverer:   Appel and Haken (1976)

============================================================
  PHILOSOPHY
============================================================

Concept:      Empiricism
Branch:       Epistemology
Definition:   All knowledge comes from sensory experience; mind is blank slate
Philosopher:  Locke/Hume
Example:      We know fire burns because we felt it, not through pure reason

Concept:      Descartes' Cogito
Branch:       Epistemology
Definition:   I think therefore I am — the one undoubtable truth
Philosopher:  Rene Descartes
Example:      Even if deceived, you must exist to be deceived

Concept:      Stoicism
Branch:       Ethics
Definition:   Focus only on what is in your control; accept all else with equanimity
Philosopher:  Marcus Aurelius/Epictetus
Example:      Illness is not in your control; your response to it is

